data.title: Seth Green breaks down his career from ‘Austin Powers’ to ‘Family Guy’ (video)
data.meta_description: Seth Green discusses his career roles including everything from ‘Buffy’ to ‘Robot Chicken’ in this Vanity Fair video.
data.text:
Seth Green breaks down the roles that make up his storied career, including those in ‘The Hotel New Hampshire,’ ‘Can’t Buy Me Love,’ ‘Buffy the Vampire Slayer,’ ‘Austin Powers: International Man of Mystery,’ ‘Austin Powers: The Spy Who Shagged Me,’ ‘Can’t Hardly Wait,’ ‘Family Guy,’ ‘Josie and the Pussycats,’ ‘The Italian Job,’ ‘Party Monster,’ ‘Entourage,’ ‘Changeland’ and ‘Robot Chicken.’ The historic 10th season finale/200th episode of ROBOT CHICKEN recently aired on Adult Swim.

See everything Green had to say in this video and check out prior celeb videos below.
